text.p: These are the leading stories in the Moroccan press on Saturday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.
- The government is to open the telecommunications sector to private investors.
- Morocco and Spain sign two accords over economic partnership.
- 5,000 workers face lay-off from telecommunications privatisation.
- Morocco and Spain negotiate 24 investment projects.
- Finance Minister Mohamed Kabbaj visited Spain to seek debt accord. He returned with promises.
